ascents.name: Progressive Disillusionment
ascents.comment:
Definitely soft if you’re tall enough to do the knee scum/left hand bump beta.

Really proud of myself for this one. I hiked two big Organics up from the gate/pavement and sent despite both my toe and tailbone not being 100%. Not too long ago that would have been more than enough to shut me down mentally, but I was able to just enjoy the process and managed to send. Gonna try and enjoy this one for a little longer than normal.

ascents.name: Beyond Life
ascents.comment:
Four days on it, 2 micro beta additions in me, and immeasurable hope.

Fell after sticking the good crimp a half dozen times, was starting to wonder if I wasn’t going to be able to finish it this trip. So. Freaking. Stoked.

ascents.name: Lactation Station
ascents.comment: This wasn’t high on my list at the start of the trip but man this thing is amazing. So fun. I think this is now one of my top 5 favorite climbs all time.

ascents.name: The Yeti
ascents.comment: Too tall/inflexible to do the high heel hook, too short to keep the left foot on for the big move. Feels quite a bit harder than most 9s I’ve done so I think I’m going with the rare upgrade.

ascents.name: Broke Ass Mofo
ascents.comment: Spent two hours trying to figure out a way to do the first move, and then once I found a sneaky knee bar it went second go, after just a classic punt since I didn’t even think a out the top out before hand.

ascents.name: Superman low
ascents.comment: Everything is aid, all climbing is contrived, and this is both rad and see-oft.

ascents.name: Johnny Appleseed
ascents.comment: Started the way the book said, soft unless you're smol.

ascents.name: Abstraction
ascents.comment: Another classic “Felt Impossible Until It Went” and then it was soft. Your classic FIUIW if you will. And you will. Shoutout Trevor for figuring out it was left hand first, and for his heroic/desperate slap onto a blank face crucial move that saved many a bootchoosle on that day.

ascents.name: Invincible
ascents.comment: Prime example of the 13th Commandment of Bouldering: "If thyne climber must travel more than 20 minutes by foot, then thou shalt make the grade soft."

ascents.name: Worm World Cave Low
ascents.comment: Today's sending shoutout goes out to Pinky and (the) Frank. Frank coming in clutch with a minor beta suggestion that lead to starting this one crossed (right hand meat wrapping the left start hold and left hand touching the right start pinch). Yup, I started crossed. What the hell. Rad.

ascents.name: Almost Famous
ascents.comment: Definitely my style, cause my style is soft. Oh and it's a good climb too.

ascents.name: The seam
ascents.comment: This things been making the rounds on Instagram recently so you just know it’s soft. 3rd go.

ascents.name: Mojo
ascents.comment: You know you're making a comeback when you can bust out the end of the day hero send. And only at the cost of lots of back of the hand skin.

ascents.name: Free Willy
ascents.comment: I didn't drive 1,000 miles to give honest grades. I came for the soft boulders and gah damn I'm taking all the points.

ascents.name: Electric Chair
ascents.comment: Can't imagine a boulder being more my style. So freaking fun. Shoutout Ryan and SDJ for letting me talk them into a night only trip and climbing until 4AM. Ya'll the realest.

ascents.name: Across the Tracks
ascents.comment: Long term project finally done! Was so surprised to have actually stuck the crux I almost punted off the top.

ascents.name: Red Rum
ascents.comment: The saga comes to an end. As much as I hate to say it, felt hard until I did it, then it felt soft.

ascents.name: *Show of hands
ascents.comment: Couple points go to Austin from CO for the deadpoint beta. Toe hooks are hard.

ascents.name: Death Scream
ascents.comment: Fun climbing. Little dabby.

ascents.name: The Practitioner
ascents.comment: Feels good to finally stop punting off the last move. Probably not 11 considering I've only done two 10s prior.

ascents.name: Beefcake
ascents.comment: Damn that's a lot of moves...

ascents.name: No Troublems
ascents.comment:
Soft UCLA rockwall v7.

Anyway, really excited about this one. Didn't expect to try it much this trip, thought I would if I finished up some old projects. But then came the rains, and it was one of the few dry or relatively dry things. Took three sessions, went first try once I got the first move, which felt fucking hard. Maybe easier if you have big hands and can pinch the right start hold easily.

ascents.name: 7 Year Cicada
ascents.comment: Hero send, so gassed. Really really rad movement. Definitely worth the hike.

ascents.name: Camel Toe
ascents.comment: Really great boulder. Full value.

ascents.name: Girls on Film Sit
ascents.comment: Might even be v8.

ascents.name: Goicochea
ascents.comment: I had a pretty good day, but definitely not better than Colin. Sending the terrible AND going on a date?! You go Colin. You. Go.

ascents.name: Aggressive Reject
ascents.comment: M soft second go since I feel like a tried this 5 years ago. Oh boy, here I got crimping again!

ascents.name: Immortal technique
ascents.comment: Something like 5 tries. Probably not 10.

ascents.name: Thunderdome
ascents.comment: Psyched to finally put this down. Thank god Alex recommended getting a right foot up for the crux, otherwise I might have never done this thing.

ascents.name: The Prism
ascents.comment: Solo sesh with a couple pads, came real close to fucking my bootchoosle up by spinning wildly on a fall. But I sacked up and sent it next burn. Actually pretty proud of myself for not getting scared and finishing it.

ascents.name: Superman
ascents.comment: Rough mental day, so psyched that I pulled this out in a session. Cool movement with a kneebar, what more could you ask for.

ascents.name: Big Chicken
ascents.comment: I thought flexibility was overrated. And then I tried Resurrection and realized there are actually some benefits to being able to get all up inside yourself.

ascents.name: Tatonka
ascents.comment: Wasted opportunity to send a climb with knee bars. Shout out the middle aged German lady who said she give me a kiss, her husband was fine AF.

ascents.name: Taxing the Pipe
ascents.comment: One of the few climbs where it actually might be better because there's a rock in the way. So fun.

ascents.name: Crimping christ on the cross
ascents.comment: I don't flash v10, but you could argue I didn't flash this since my head hit the dab rock.

ascents.name: Dirty Martini on the rocks
ascents.comment: Had to wait for some big strong men to come spot me because those topout holds look like choss, sound like choss, and quack like choss. But somehow they didn't break.

ascents.name: Solo Endeavors
ascents.comment: So freaking fun.

ascents.name: Crimps of Wrath
ascents.comment: Kian's ability to make dolphin sounds is unprecedented. Also this mantle is sweat as.

ascents.name: Blurred Lines
ascents.comment: If you asked a trad climber to come up with a boulder that perfectly encapsulates how dumb bouldering is, this would probably be the product.

ascents.name: Fat Guy in a Little Coat
ascents.comment: Crazy boulder, fun moves. Wrecked from night climbing but managed to pull out yet another Iwo send.

ascents.name: Ashy To Classy
ascents.comment: Started on the lowest holds under the center of the face. 19 hand moves from the sit good lord, what am I sport climbing?

ascents.name: Skeeter Glen
ascents.comment: Sometimes I have these epiphanies that maybe I'm not that smart. How could I have not realized that a boulder with "Skeeter" in the name was going to be a breeding ground for mosquitoes? Despite that, really fun climb, highly recommend. Just not in the middle of summer.

ascents.name: Whale Tail
ascents.comment: Classic Jenny, says we can come stay at her cabin, turns out it's like a hostel and we end up sleeping in a parking lot. 7/10 would sleep there again though.

ascents.name: Bitch Slap 5
ascents.comment: Hero send right before dark. Shout out the sandbox for hauling pads up the hill, especially since I got us super lost...

ascents.name: Honor Among Thieves
ascents.comment: Solo sesh, really good bouldah.

ascents.name: Scare Tactics Right
ascents.comment: Good movement, better than the regular line?

ascents.name: Cholos
ascents.comment: Never thought I'd be able to do this, nice finger test.

ascents.name: Out Of Your League
ascents.comment: 5 or 6 tries. Feels impossible until you do it.

ascents.name: Pepsi Challenge sit
ascents.comment: Definitely my style. Great climb.

ascents.name: Space Cowboy
ascents.comment: Two things: 1) How this is v9 and Space Race is v7, I'll never know. Legit couldn't do the 7. 2) Really glad I didn't pull the really good left hand crimp/pinch off onto my face. That thing is gonna blow.

ascents.name: Pimp Juice
ascents.comment: Quality boulder with an even better view. And we didn't even get lost!

ascents.name: Worst Case Scenario
ascents.comment: Strained my shoulder on the send burn. But it's ok, totally worth it to be mostly unable to climb with 5 days left in the trip. Totally worth it. Yup. Completely. Totally. Worth. It.

ascents.name: The Giving Tree
ascents.comment: A+ problem. Definitely sent because of pillow talk on crash pad island the night before.

ascents.name: Power Of Geometry
ascents.comment: Erik sending the stand was partially because of my tricep workout. You're welcome.

ascents.name: Conan
ascents.comment: What an eventful 48 hours...

ascents.name: The Force
ascents.comment: 5 pads, no spotters. "And what happened, then? Well, in Oakland they say- that Mr. Dangle's small balls grew three sizes that day. And then- the true meaning of sending came through, and Mr. Dangle found the strength of ten Dangles, plus two!"

ascents.name: Pugilist
ascents.comment: Hey I still sorta know how to rock climb.

ascents.name: Playmate of the Year
ascents.comment: Big day.

ascents.name: Resident evil
ascents.comment: Super finicky. Never felt hard, just couldn't put it together.

ascents.name: Musashi
ascents.comment: Improbable send, feels like you're going to fall off every move. Red crew send train. First climb I've done before Daniel?

ascents.name: The Coffee Cup
ascents.comment: Scrunchy foot beta fo life.

ascents.name: Sesame Street
ascents.comment: Sent right before we left Squamish, and after seeing Leavenworth, we may not go back. Pretty great way to leave.

ascents.name: Worm World Cave
ascents.comment: Finally able to finish it. Really cool climb. Almost turned into another Soul Slinger situation with Guim.

ascents.name: Left Hand of Darkness
ascents.comment: Surprise send, wasn't really planning to get on it. And only blew the last move once...

ascents.name: Byron's Roof
ascents.comment: The saga is finally over. Punted off the top out way to many times...

ascents.name: Soul Caliber
ascents.comment: Consolation prize after punting off Byron's... again...

ascents.name: Chupamihuevos stand
ascents.comment: Probably v8 when it's cold. Sit seems like a cooler line than the stand.

ascents.name: Soul Slinger
ascents.comment: The saga is finally over. Don't think I would have ever done this if SOUP man hadn't shown me the wide pinch beta.

ascents.name: Michael Caine
ascents.comment: Jesus, talk about punting. Jimmy from Alabama and "SOUP!" man gave me some new beta for Soul Slinger, better watch out Guim, it's gonna go.

ascents.name: Cocktail Sauce
ascents.comment: Oh man. So proud.

ascents.name: Last Dance
ascents.comment: I think this is the one I did. Cool movement.

ascents.name: Acid Wash
ascents.comment: I don't think this is a 10 if you have the height.

ascents.name: Twin Cracks
ascents.comment: Awesome climb. Sent after it got dark, had the car running so I could use the high beams to light it up.

ascents.name: Sesame Street Direct
ascents.comment: Two tries this year, shoulda done it last year. Good first day of the trip, spirits were high,  and then all hell broke loose...

ascents.name: Chuckie's torture
ascents.comment: 3rd or 4th try. Definitely soft. Fun.

ascents.name: Water Hazard Right
ascents.comment: Could probably just be called an eight. Less than an hour of work. Movement isn't too bad though.

ascents.name: Acid Wash Right
ascents.comment: Felt good to try that hard on the first move. Probably not a 9 but still felt hard to me

ascents.name: Golden Plates
ascents.comment: Both better and harder than I expected.

ascents.name: No Substance
ascents.comment: I can’t stop splitting tips, but at least I can still throw down some old projects. Stoked.

ascents.name: The Flu
ascents.comment: Shoutout Will and Joaquin for sussing all the beta. Only reason I was able to flash.

ascents.name: Black Sea
ascents.comment: Better than expected.

ascents.name: Thor's Hammer
ascents.comment: So sick. This is definitely going to be one of the most popular 8s once it’s more known.

ascents.name: Tubesnake Boogie
ascents.comment: Fairly terrifying. I hope those last flake crimps never rip...

ascents.name: Cow Bell
ascents.comment: Better than I expected.

ascents.name: Smoke Em If Ya Got Em
ascents.comment: Good climb, didn't feel close to v10 for me. The crux was hiking to the boulder.

ascents.name: Foxy Lady
ascents.comment: Surprisingly tough.

ascents.name: Olde Glory
ascents.comment: Might be even better than the direct line? Not too much harder.

ascents.name: Drunk Tank
ascents.comment: This climb is so weird, and has so many uncomfortable/strange holds, that it was actually fun. Recommended.

ascents.name: Body Glove
ascents.comment: Gave the single most girly scream of my life going for the slot jug up top. Not my proudest moment, but I sent. And that, dear readers, is more meaningful.

ascents.name: The Strainer
ascents.comment: Really good bouldah. Also this as the same grade as Mad Max? Loooooool.

ascents.name: The Drill Sergeant
ascents.comment: This is the type of problem you only do if you’re chasing points or are bored waiting for your friends. Obviously I was the former.

ascents.name: Mosquito Incubator
ascents.comment: Figured out all the moves yesterday but punted off the top and got pretty dejected. Then I managed to bruise my left foot and tweak my right knee on The Weasel, so psych was lower than my Grundle Me This season expectations. Managed to turn this frown upside down and have a pretty successful day today. There is hope.

ascents.name: The Bulb
ascents.comment: Quested HARD on the top out slab but managed to keep it together. And good thing too cause ho boy that fall woulda sucked.

ascents.name: Master Blaster
ascents.comment: Consolation for getting railed by the Yeti again.

ascents.name: Sunkist
ascents.comment: Very much my style, but also very soft. I’ll take the points though, pretty physically and mentally wrecked today.

ascents.name: Zun Zun
ascents.comment: Apparently waking up at 5 am to climb means I crash at 1.

ascents.name: Buttload of Sausage
ascents.comment: Couldn’t put down Yeti but managed to send all the 8s at Woods lake in a day. Fitness day, fitness day, fitness day.

ascents.name: The Ninth Wave
ascents.comment: You know what, for a climb with such a high dab potential and a constant scent of pee, this thing is pretty sweet as.

ascents.name: Ultramega
ascents.comment: That's too many moves. You can't have that many moves on a boulder, unless your name is "Too many moves". Then you can have too many moves. But no more.

ascents.name: Bad Religion
ascents.comment: Wow, I am awful at toe hooks. Good thing technique only matters on slab.

ascents.name: Something Different
ascents.comment: Couldn't do Paul's wizard like heel hook beta. Went with the gym baby style instead.

ascents.name: Integrity
ascents.comment: Soft, but oh so perfect compression.

ascents.name: Mean green
ascents.comment: For some reason I never logged this?

ascents.name: Hand Grenade
ascents.comment: I never new how utterly terrible I am at knee bars. Time to train for Heuco.

ascents.name: Down Syndrome
ascents.comment: Shouda flashed. Can't believe it took me just as long as it took Charlie.

ascents.name: Hotos and Hand Tools
ascents.comment: I don't know if I started in the right spot, but regardless: soft.

ascents.name: Kids These Days
ascents.comment: After hiking all the way up to The Main Attraction only to find it with a river running underneath it, we went back down and hopped on this. So good! This climb alone makes the hike worth it.

ascents.name: Pie Priority
ascents.comment: The scoop to the right of high priority. Start left hand on the obvious crimp/pinch and right on the juggy arete hold. Now, I'm not saying it's better than high priority... because it's obviously not.

ascents.name: Ultimate Trogdor
ascents.comment: Ultimate Trogdor is the best V8 in California, 1v1 me you straight willn't.

ascents.name: Disco Diva
ascents.comment: I feel like this one is easy for everyone. Except me.

ascents.name: Detached
ascents.comment: Only flashed because I don't climb, I just train, and this is basically a campus board.

ascents.name: The Seam
ascents.comment: Ryan and Chase passed up this to keep trying the glorified campus board. Good thing too since this was just choss.

ascents.name: Fujiyama Sit
ascents.comment: Oh god. So many mosquitos.

ascents.name: The Gerbler
ascents.comment: 60% sure I started in the right spot. 100% sure this thing is meh.

ascents.name: PJ Tight
ascents.comment: I hope something broke, because otherwise lol v10.

ascents.name: Poseidon
ascents.comment: Sent while snowing, so cool. At least my shoulder didn't completely prevent me from climbing...

ascents.name: Solitaire
ascents.comment: Only climb I did all weekend was two jump moves. Clearly I need more athleticism. Shoutout Canadians, they're super nice.

ascents.name: Brian's Project
ascents.comment: Nice to put down an old project despite having a hurt finger. Now to get healthy for the return trip in 3 weeks.

ascents.name: Lost, But not forgotten
ascents.comment: Ryan said he would come, but he didn't. But Ryan, you said!

ascents.name: Fear and Loathing in Tuolumne
ascents.comment: Amazed I could still climb after hiking to Marioulumne. Holy balls.

ascents.name: Israil Direct
ascents.comment: That's a big span.

ascents.name: Reduced fat milk
ascents.comment: Interesting.

ascents.name: They Call Him Jordan
ascents.comment: Maybe if I wasn't so white I would have jumped.

ascents.name: The Lion's Den
ascents.comment: I think team California is ready for Utah...

ascents.name: War of God
ascents.comment: I thought this one was harder than the right...

ascents.name: Aries: God of War
ascents.comment: The 45 minute hike uphill sucks, but damn there are some great lines here...

ascents.name: The Rubik's Cube
ascents.comment: Back smear beta is best beta.

ascents.name: Kobe Tai
ascents.comment: Much cooler than it first looked.

ascents.name: Busted
ascents.comment: Not bad, climbs pretty well.

ascents.name: Pretty Hate Machine
ascents.comment: Really good line. Top of the list for v8 climber's in Leavenworth, behind only Pimpsqueak?

ascents.name: Missing In Action
ascents.comment: Great climb, wet holds almost meant ripping a new butt hole from the top.

ascents.name: Native American Giver
ascents.comment: Should have finished last year, surprisingly frustrating.

ascents.name: Resurrection
ascents.comment: Weird first slap move. An ok climb.

ascents.name: Cole's Corner
ascents.comment: Zero stars. Even used a sideways dyno, which sounds sick, but wasn't. Also, Hanta Man is a terrible climb, and the Sail is really bad too.

ascents.name: Pimpsqueak
ascents.comment: If this is v9, consider me, Miles Davis. But yea, it's a pretty good climb.

ascents.name: Scrambled Eggs
ascents.comment: I really like this thing...

ascents.name: Soul Snatch
ascents.comment: Maybe 7. I am a worthless climber when it's hot.

ascents.name: Meadow Roof
ascents.comment: Cool climb, especially with the non-reachy beta. Elevation definitely a factor.

ascents.name: Checkerboard
ascents.comment: Second go from the start after trying the stand once. Amazing line, great way to finish off the season.

ascents.name: Junior's achievement
ascents.comment: Hella crimpy. Surprise send.

ascents.name: Big K
ascents.comment: I'm really bad at climbing.

ascents.name: Bitch Slap Left
ascents.comment: Tall beta is the way to go.

ascents.name: Monkey Bar Direct
ascents.comment: I win the ugliest ascent award...

ascents.name: Hunger
ascents.comment: Cool little climb.

ascents.name: Gleaming the cube
ascents.comment: Only did this because David did it, and I can't be having him do eights that I haven't.

ascents.name: Crimp Ladder Extension
ascents.comment: Wow that took way too long... Regular version is better.

ascents.name: Gibb's Cave
ascents.comment: Finally. Been trying for three years. Tried the high right heelhook beta and it worked much better than the low one.

ascents.name: Mantra
ascents.comment: Should be renamed to "Madge Padge". Atleast according to Jaqui.

ascents.name: Gluttony
ascents.comment: Avenging the death of my index finger last week.

ascents.name: Torque Spanner
ascents.comment: Hah.

ascents.name: Crystal Method
ascents.comment: Solid for the grade. Great movement. Great climb.

ascents.name: Boxcar arete
ascents.comment: Cool. My style.

ascents.name: Fly Boy Sit
ascents.comment: Awesome line. Used the intermediate which makes the last move a bit less intimidating.

ascents.name: Can opener
ascents.comment: Height dependent. I was able to bump from the first left hand side pull/undercling all the way to some good crimps up high.

ascents.name: Autobody
ascents.comment: Classic. A must see.

ascents.name: Pandemic
ascents.comment: Little reachy.

ascents.name: Bring the Heatwole
ascents.comment: You know what they say, three stars for kneebars.

ascents.name: Boysize
ascents.comment: Short but fun.

ascents.name: Baldwin Bash
ascents.comment: Fun.

ascents.name: One Eye Willie
ascents.comment: Couldn’t remember if I had done this one.

ascents.name: Cellulite Eliminator Sit
ascents.comment: Drew assuming the position between your legs is peak sexiness, change my view.

ascents.name: Crescendo
ascents.comment: This might be my first soft second go. Noice.

ascents.name: Stupid Arete
ascents.comment: This is simultaneously both stupid and not stupid. Pretty good movement, but like... you top out on another boulder? Weird...

ascents.name: Twister
ascents.comment: Climbs better than I expected.

ascents.name: The hourglass
ascents.comment: Met some people at the boulder and with in 10 minutes a girl was telling us about one time when she shit herself while climbing. A+ atmosphere, would climb again.

ascents.name: Backdoor Ass Attack
ascents.comment: Good problem, great name.

ascents.name: Mindbender
ascents.comment: Feels impossible until you BEND your MIND into believing you can do it. Get it? Guys? Anybody?

ascents.name: A.T.D.
ascents.comment: I’ve wanted to do this one for the longest time solely for the name. Projected for like 1.5 hours with Lloyd and Johnny and then Allen comes out of fucking nowhere and flashes it with, objectively, shit beta. Classic.

ascents.name: Golden Boy
ascents.comment: Soft?! Gah damn Squamish guidebook, you sandy AF.

ascents.name: Bapst
ascents.comment: Almost a great problem, just a little awkward.

ascents.name: Human Math
ascents.comment: Started from the lowest jug. Way in the hole. Amazing boulder, I heart squeezing.

ascents.name: Mr. Mackey
ascents.comment: Gotta love the camaraderie trips with the boyz.

ascents.name: Daily Dick Dose
ascents.comment: Meh.

ascents.name: Babyface
ascents.comment: Super good/

ascents.name: Speedbump
ascents.comment: Felt super hard until I got the micro beta from Emily. And then it, classically, felt soft.

ascents.name: New Religion
ascents.comment: How those crimp flakes are still on the wall is beyond me. But they are sweet. as.

ascents.name: So Close
ascents.comment: Doesn't look like much but damn did it end up being hard...

ascents.name: Sesh Carter
ascents.comment: Pretty good, the sit seems no existent to me...

ascents.name: Long Distance Girl
ascents.comment: Pretty good, little reachy? All climbs are better when lit up with floodies at night.

ascents.name: Slam Dunk
ascents.comment: Good movement, taller than I expected. Quality.

ascents.name: Drunk With Power
ascents.comment: I'm starting to forget what it's like to climb in sub 80 degree temps and without mosquitoes.

ascents.name: Immaculate Conception
ascents.comment: Hard unless you're tall? Nothing like a real good soul climbing sesh to get you to believe in some smeary feet.

ascents.name: Evan and Amy
ascents.comment: Old man Barron can still pull out a few new tricks. Had to strip down to my skivvys and take a swig of Maker's Mark to get the send. Shoutout Davy for the beta, and the sandbox for their support. Sometimes you can just put it with ya hand on it.

ascents.name: Midnight Train
ascents.comment: Shoutout Ryan for bringing the sandbox together for one of the best weekends ever. And shoutout Sarah for letting us use her family's cabin. Ya the real MVPs.

ascents.name: Powersauce
ascents.comment: It's boulders like this that really make you question how dumb this hobby is.

ascents.name: Sugar Babies
ascents.comment: Paul didn't added his send but didn't add a comment? Must be afraid of what JOHN CENA WOULD THINK OF IT.

ascents.name: Cindy Swank
ascents.comment: What a #sweetboy problem.

ascents.name: Four Horsemen
ascents.comment: Fun compression. Top out to the left if you like stepping on chossy knobs!

ascents.name: Reach for a peach
ascents.comment: Punted off the top twice before sending. Not one of my finer moments.

ascents.name: High Priority
ascents.comment: Ended up walking about 6 miles round trip. Dear god these boulders are far. But there is definitely some quality lines out there.

ascents.name: 3am at denny's
ascents.comment: Wow. That is one. soft. piece. of aaacee. I know, from experience.

ascents.name: The Wind Below
ascents.comment: Amazing. So proud of Stoffel for putting it down despite no finger tips.

ascents.name: Blue Lambo
ascents.comment: Watch out for surprise poops.

ascents.name: Dark Continent
ascents.comment: You can buy a 4 bedroom house in Orangeville for 50k... next investment?

ascents.name: No Holds Bard
ascents.comment: Remember it feeling really hard, not too bad this time.

ascents.name: Asian Invasion
ascents.comment: I thought this thing was tall for some reason...

ascents.name: For the Glory
ascents.comment: Sandbox sendfest 2015.

ascents.name: White Stuff
ascents.comment: Expected the White Stuff to be a bit stickier...

ascents.name: Jedi Jake sit
ascents.comment: Erik and I got super lost looking for this thing. Awesome boulder, excellent climb. Erik can frash the sit next time for sure!

ascents.name: Silly Roof
ascents.comment: Believe it or not, this roof is silly. Also totally almost greased off the top which would have, uhhh, been ill advised.

ascents.name: G2-07
ascents.comment: Revenge for 3 years ago.

ascents.name: Electric Fence
ascents.comment: Climbing's easier when people figure out the beta for you. Couple points go to Tom and Guim

ascents.name: SPAM
ascents.comment: Eliminate. So it's supa classic.

ascents.name: Phoney Baloney
ascents.comment: Guim's mega proj.

ascents.name: Big Boy
ascents.comment: So assthetic.

ascents.name: Stand up
ascents.comment: Punted off the full line. Classic Scott

ascents.name: Tin Man Sit
ascents.comment: Great climb. The sit doesn't add much but is the obvious start.

ascents.name: Raging Bull
ascents.comment: Not bad.

ascents.name: Off the Couch
ascents.comment: Fun crimpy line.

ascents.name: The Shield
ascents.comment: Good climb, one hardish move.

ascents.name: Dangle
ascents.comment: Weird mantle to topout.

ascents.name: Breakfast at Tiffany's
